  <marc:subfield code="a">Script:  Written in a vocalized Provenc&#x327;al semi-cursive script in the hand of &#x2BB;Imanu&#x2BC;el ben Gad de Milhaud, a scribe who created many manuscripts for prayers in the customs of French communities in the late 17th and early 18th centuries.</marc:subfield>
</marc:datafield>
    <marc:datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="500">
  <marc:subfield code="a">Binding: Later binding, cheap leather, approximately 1850. The binding doesn't fit the manuscript and it has insect damage.</marc:subfield>
</marc:datafield>
    <marc:datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="500">
  <marc:subfield code="a">Origin:  Written possibly in Carpentras, certainly in the Comtat Venaissin, by &#x2BB;Imanu&#x2BC;el ben Gad de Milhaud on 2 Sivan 5423 (Thursday, 7 June 1663).</marc:subfield>
